Taiwan Premier Sean Chen accepted the
resignation of Finance Minister Christina Liu, Cabinet spokesman
Hu Yu-wei said by phone today.  Liu on May 29 announced her resignation after disagreeing
with legislators from the ruling Kuomintang party over a
proposed capital gains tax.  The Cabinet names deputy finance minister Tseng Ming-chung
as acting Finance Minister, it said in an e-mailed statement
today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
